RGC <- fread(file="human_fRGC_pRGC/SCP839/expression/Human_retina_combined_all_expression_matrix.csv")  %>% as.data.frame()
row.names(RGC) <- RGC$V1


#import cluster file
clustered_RGC <-
  read.delim(
    "human_fRGC_pRGC/SCP839/cluster/HumanRGC_clusterfile.txt",
    header = F,
    sep = "\t",
    dec = "."
  )

clustered_RGC = clustered_RGC[-1,]
clustered_RGC = clustered_RGC[-1,]

#assign RGC cluster info to expression file
RGC= RGC %>% select(clustered_RGC$V1)
#build the suerat object
Human_Object = CreateSeuratObject(
  RGC,
  project = "SeuratProject",
  assay = "RNA",  min.cells = 1,
  min.features = 1
)
# rename 13 fRFC clusters to a foveal group
#n_f = 'foveal'

n_f = 'fRGC'
Human_Object <- RenameIdents(
  Human_Object,
  'H11FoveaS1' = n_f,
  'H2Fovea1S1' = n_f,
  'H2Fovea2S1' = n_f,
  'H3FoveaS1' = n_f,
  'H3FoveaS2' = n_f,
  'H3FoveaS3' = n_f,
  'H4FoveaS1' = n_f,
  'H5FoveaS1' = n_f,
  'H5FoveaS2' = n_f,
  'H5FoveaS3' = n_f,
  'H5FoveaS4' = n_f,
  'H5FoveaS5' = n_f,
  'H9FoveaS1' = n_f
)
# rename 6 pRGC clusters to a peripheial group
n_p = 'peripheral'


n_p = 'pRGC'
Human_Object <- RenameIdents(
  Human_Object,
  'H1CD73dpS1' = n_p,
  'H1CD90S1' = n_p,
  'H3CD73dpS1' = n_p,
  'H3CD73dpS2' = n_p,
  'H3CD90S1' = n_p,
  'H3CD90S2' = n_p
)
#gene differential analysis between foveal and peripheral cell 

MAST_Human_10 = FindMarkers(
  Human_Object ,
  ident.1 = "fRGC",
  ident.2 = "pRGC",
  test.use = "MAST" ,
  logfc.threshold = 0.13,
  assay = "RNA",
  verbose = FALSE
)

GSEA

library(edgeR)
library(DESeq2)
library(fgsea)
library(clusterProfiler)
library(enrichplot)
library(ggplot2)
library(ggpubr)
library(export)



# GSEA USING ALL Genome June 14 ,
# GEST hallmark


# get the genome wide fold change table and sort
human_fold = FoldChange(Human_Object,
                        ident.1 = "fRGC",
                        ident.2 = "pRGC")

human_fold <- human_fold[order(-human_fold$avg_log2FC), ]
#human_fold$avg_log2FC = rownames(human_fold)


id_human_all <- human_fold$avg_log2FC
names(id_human_all) <- rownames(human_fold)
## fgsea with hallmark, GMT file from http://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb/index.jsp
gmtfile <- "h.all.v2023.1.Hs.symbols.gmt"
hallmark <- read.gmt(gmtfile)
hallmark$term <- gsub('HALLMARK_', '', hallmark$term)
hallmark.list <- hallmark %>% split(.$term) %>% lapply("[[", 2)


## Perform the fgsea analysis
set.seed(98177)
fgseaRes <- fgsea(
  pathways = hallmark.list,
  stats = id_human_all,
  minSize = 1,
  maxSize = 10000,
  nperm = 10000
)
sig_h  <- fgseaRes[fgseaRes$padj < 0.05, ]
sig_h <- sig_h[order(sig_h$NES, decreasing = T), ]

sig_h

# import counting table


fRGC <-  fread("~/Macaque_fov_RGC_expression.txt")  %>% as.data.frame()
row.names(fRGC) <- fRGC$GENE
fRGC = fRGC[,-1]

pRGC <-  fread("~/Macaque_per_RGC_expression.txt")  %>% as.data.frame()
row.names(pRGC) <- pRGC$GENE
pRGC = pRGC[,-1]
# Set up fRGC object
fRGC <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = fRGC, project = "fRGC")
Idents(object = fRGC)  = 'foveal'
#fRGC$compare <- "fRGC"


# Set up pRGC object
pRGC <- CreateSeuratObject(counts = pRGC, project = "pRGC")
Idents(object = pRGC) <- 'peripheral'
#pRGC$compare <- "pRGC"
# Merge the two Seurat objects
merged_seurat <- merge(pRGC, fRGC)
merged_seurat@active.ident <- factor(x = merged_seurat@active.ident, levels = c('peripheral', 'foveal'))

merged_seurat@meta.data$stim <- c(rep("peripheral", ncol(pRGC)), rep("foveal", ncol(fRGC)))
#gene differential analysis between foveal and peripheral cell 
MAST_Macaque_20_1 = FindMarkers(merged_seurat, ident.1 = "foveal", ident.2 = "peripheral",
                              logfc.threshold = 0.13,test.use = "MAST",verbose = FALSE)
MAST_Macaque_20_1$Gene = rownames(MAST_Macaque_20_1)
#gene differential analysis between foveal and peripheral cell 
MAST_Macaque_20_2 = FindMarkers(merged_seurat, ident.1 = "foveal", ident.2 = "peripheral",
                              logfc.threshold = 0.24,test.use = "MAST",verbose = FALSE)
MAST_Macaque_20_2$Gene = rownames(MAST_Macaque_20_2)


# Round p-values to 1 decimal place
MAST_Macaque_20_2$p_val <- round(MAST_Macaque_20_2$p_val, digits = 1)
MAST_Macaque_20_2$p_val_adj <- round(MAST_Macaque_20_2$p_val_adj, digits = 1)

## fgsea for hallmark 
setwd("~/")


gmtfile <- "./msigdb.v2022.1.Mm.symbols.gmt"

hallmark <- read.gmt(gmtfile)
hallmark$term <- gsub('HALLMARK_','',hallmark$term)
hallmark.list <- hallmark %>% split(.$term) %>% lapply( "[[", 2)




## Perform the fgsea analysis
set.seed(98177)
fgseaRes <-fgseaMultilevel(pathways = hallmark.list, 
                           stats = id_Macaque_all,
                           minSize=1,
                           maxSize=10000)

sig_Macaque <- fgseaRes[fgseaRes$padj<0.05,]
sig_Macaque <- sig_Macaque[order(sig_Macaque$NES,decreasing = T),]

## plot
plotGseaTable(hallmark.list[sig_Macaque$pathway],id, fgseaRes,gseaParam = 0.5)

Violin plots for comparison of HIF1A,OPTN,SOD1,IFI6 in human / macaque data

# PPT for violin plot

p = VlnPlot(
  Human_Object,
  features = c('HIF1A','OPTN','SOD1','IFI6'),
  assay = "RNA",
  pt.size = 0,
  ncol = 4
) 
p

p2 = VlnPlot(
  merged_seurat,
  features = c('HIF1A','OPTN','SOD1','IFI6'),
  assay = "RNA",
  pt.size = 0,
  ncol = 4
) 
p2 

library(ggpubr)
multi.page <- ggarrange(p, p2,
                        nrow = 2, 
                        ncol = 1) + ggtitle("Human(top) and Monkey(down)") + theme(plot.title = element_text(lineheight=.8, face="bold"))


multi.page
